001package gbw.melange.common.elementary.types;
002
003/**
004 * Represents empty space. If a nearby element has {@link gbw.melange.common.elementary.contraints.SizingPolicy#FIT_CONTENT}, it will take priority in terms of space use.
005 *
006 * @author GustavBW
007 * @version $Id: $Id
008 */
009public interface ISpacerElement extends IConstrainedElement {
010    /**
011     * <p>getRequestedHeight.</p>
012     *
013     * @return a double
014     */
015    double getRequestedHeight();
016    /**
017     * <p>getRequestedWidth.</p>
018     *
019     * @return a double
020     */
021    double getRequestedWidth();
022}
